Frank Smutniak at FlyBase Harvard developed the converter between 
GAME XML and chado XML formats, which is included as part of XML-XORT package in XML-XORT/conf/
command for GameBridge convertor:(CTG: convert Chado XML into GAME xml, 
GTC: convert GAME into chado xml)

1. java classpath $path_to_GameChadoConv.jar GTC GTC game_file chado_file

2. then you can load it into chadoDB with
perl XML-XORT/bin/xort_loader.pl ...

3. to dump out data from chadoDB into chadoxml, 
  perl XML-XORT/bin/xort_dump.pl ....
  we use the dumpspec XML-XORT/examples/dumpspec_apollo.xml
  see XML-XORT/examples/apollo_chado.pl for how to use it.

in XML-XORT/conf, there are a few dumpspec using for FlyBase, you can edit to adopt your need

4. to convert from chadoXML to gameXML:
  java classpath $path_to_GameChadoConv.jar CTG chado_file game_file


the jar file come with this package  XML-XORT/conf/GameChadoConv.jar
CTG
        -a
                //convert all
        -g
                //convert genes only
        -c
                //convert comp anal only
GTC
        -a
                //convert all
        -g
                //convert genes only
        -c
                //convert comp anal only
        -t
                //convert transactional changes only
        -p
                //INCL Transposable Elements
        -R
                //SPECIAL HANDLING for rel4
        -H
                //SPECIAL HANDLING for Heterochromatin (pick up users provided aa 
                // instead of calculated aa which is default)




